{"summary": "A custom Babel plugin `inject-source-location.js` injects `__sourceLocation` / `__sourcelocation` props onto every JSX element at build time, which React then rejects on web because those props leak through to native DOM elements.", "layer": "frontend", "root_cause": "In `babel.config.js`, when `EXPO_PUBLIC_ENABLE_EDIT_MODE=TRUE` and `NODE_ENV=development`, two custom Babel plugins are loaded: `babel-plugins/editable-elements.js` and `babel-plugins/inject-source-location.js`. The second plugin annotates every JSX element with a `__sourceLocation` prop (and its lowercase variant `__sourcelocation`) so the edit-mode UI can identify component origins. React Native components that render to the web DOM (e.g. `<View>`, `<Text>`, `<Pressable>`) pass these unknown props down to their underlying HTML elements (`<div>`, `<span>`, etc.), which React DOM does not recognise. React then fires the warning: \"React does not recognize the `__sourceLocation` prop on a DOM element.\" The warning fires on every rendered component tree node, which is why it appears immediately at app startup on the Web platform only.", "evidence": "[2026-06-20T15:49:03.839Z] [Web] [ERROR] React does not recognize the `%s` prop on a DOM element. If you intentionally want it to appear in the DOM as a custom attribute, spell it as lowercase `%s` instead. If you accidentally passed it from a parent component, remove it from the DOM element. __c...\n(message truncated by log collector; prop name resolves to `__sourceLocation` / `__sourcelocation` based on babel.config.js lines 8-10 loading `babel-plugins/inject-source-location.js`)", "recommended_action": "The `inject-source-location.js` Babel plugin must filter out the injected props before they reach DOM host elements. Two concrete fixes: (1) In the plugin itself, only inject `__sourceLocation` onto custom React components (capitalised JSX tags), never onto lowercase host elements like `div`, `span`, `input`, etc. (2) Alternatively, in every React Native web component that wraps a DOM element, destructure and discard `__sourceLocation` / `__sourcelocation` before spreading props onto the DOM node. The quickest safe fix is option (1) — add a check in `babel-plugins/inject-source-location.js` so the prop is only added when `openingElement.name` starts with an uppercase letter or is a member expression (i.e. a React component, not a DOM tag).", "confidence": "high"}

